com.dropbox.sync.android

Class DbxPath

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.dropbox.sync.android.DbxPath
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Comparable<DbxPath>

    public final class DbxPath
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.lang.Comparable<DbxPath>
    Represents a path in Dropbox, relative to your App Folder.

    Dropbox paths always begin with a forward-slash, representing the root of your App Folder, and use forward-slashes to separate components. Mixed-case is allowed, but comparisons are case-insensitive.

    Some special names, characters, or encodings aren't allowed in a Dropbox path, and will result in an InvalidPathException. Others are allowed, but may not sync properly to all platforms. For more details see this article.

    • Field Detail

      • ROOT

        public static final DbxPath ROOT
        Dropbox paths always begin with a forward-slash and ROOT is always a single forward-slash. Note that the Sync API only supports the App Folder permission and ROOT refers to the root of your app's folder.

      • DbxPath

        public DbxPath(DbxPath parent,
       java.lang.String childName)
        throws DbxPath.InvalidPathException
        Creates a new DbxPath representing a child or descendant of a parent path.
        • DbxPath(ROOT, "Photos") → "/Photos"
        • DbxPath(DbxPath("/Photos/Recent"), "Home.jpg") → "/Photos/Recent/Home.jpg"
        • DbxPath(DbxPath("/Photos"), "Recent/Home.jpg") → "/Photos/Recent/Home.jpg"
        Parameters:
        parent - the parent path
        childName - the name or sub-path for the new child
        Throws:
        DbxPath.InvalidPathException - if name isn't a legal Dropbox path
